AU  - Kircher, Philipp
AU  - Muller, Paul
T1  - Providing Advice to Jobseekers at Low Cost: An Experimental Study on Online Advice
PY  - 2019
Y1  - 2019/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdy059
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 86
IS  - 4
SP  - 1411
EP  - 1447
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We develop and evaluate experimentally a novel tool that redesigns the job search process by providing tailored advice at low cost. We invited jobseekers to our computer facilities for twelve consecutive weekly sessions to search for real jobs on our web interface. For one-half, instead of relying on their own search criteria, we use readily available labour market data to display relevant alternative occupations and associated jobs. The data indicate that this broadens the set of jobs they consider and increases their job interviews especially for participants who otherwise search narrowly and have been unemployed for a few months.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdy059
ER  - 



